bib_record.title: The photodisintegration of Li-6 and Li-7.

free_txt: The photodisintegration   of   the   stable   lithium
isotopes  were investigated for protons,  deuterons,
tritons, He3 and alpha particles which were detected
and identified up to 20 MeV particle energy. Angular
distributions were measured using g-ray energies  up
to  eg=50 MeV.  Those were compared with theoretical
predictions and with other experiments. A remarkable
low  (g,t)-cross section was found for both isotopes
in  disagreement  to  previous  measurements   using
